d:** `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be`\n**Frontend:** `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n**DB:** dtlx on mongodb://103.253.21.98:27017\n\n### Pet Connect (archived/inactive)\nCodebase exists but no active development.\n\n## Pending Tasks\n\n### Active (as of 2026-04-12 06:47 UTC)\n- **Stitch MCP async polling**: wrapper với\n\nSource: MEMORY.md#L1-L44","source":"memory","citation":"MEMORY.md#L1-L44","corpus":"memory"}],"provider":"none","citations":"auto","mode":"fts-only"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775979983219}}
{"type":"message","id":"3dbf4c7d","parentId":"f703b76a","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:46:26.234Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory doesn't have specific context about Confluence MCP or GitLab MCP from recent sessions. Let me check the sessions_history for the direct session to get more context.","thinkingSignature":"f8b5d4a9bc7439135ac8a97a71ee703dcbdad6e5886200961568c7bfc74420e3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xxwxt2q71phy_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","limit":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":85,"cacheRead":15757,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15842,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979983450,"responseId":"062a80d0afe807c3c6abba8acb1c0cae"}}
{"type":"message","id":"926e427e","parentId":"3dbf4c7d","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:46:27.061Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xxwxt2q71phy_1","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I see the issue clearly. The process with PID 358696 is `openclaw` (not `openclaw-gateway`) and PID 358706 is `openclaw-gateway`. There are two processes:\\n\\n1. `openclaw` (PID 358696) - started at 07:35\\n2. `openclaw-gateway` (PID 358706) - started at 07:35\\n\\nBoth started at 07:35 when I ran `systemctl restart`. The ERROR messages at 07:35:25 are from the new `openclaw` process trying to start with the old config (which still had `mcpServers`).\\n \\nThe reload at 07:35:28 picked up my config changes and detected the new confluence server, but the gateway couldn't fully restart because there were active operations running at the time. Then at 07:36:02, the gateway successfully reloaded the updated configuration.\\n\\nSo the gateway is actually running fine now with my new config that includes confluence. The ERROR logs I was seeing earlier were from before I removed `mcpServers` from the config. I should test whether the confluence MCP tools are actually working by making a direct MCP call through the gateway's WebSocket API.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Gateway đã reload thành công với `mcp.servers.confluence`. Test trực tiếp:\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_tvbx6yfm0m32_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"NODE_PATH=/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/node_modules node << 'EOF'\\nconst WebSocket = require('ws');\\n\\nconst ws = new WebSocket('ws://127.0.0.1:18789');\\nlet id = 1;\\n\\nws.on('open', () => {\\n  ws.send(JSON.stringify({ method: 'auth.anonymous', params: {}, id: id++ }));\\n});\\n\\nws.on('message', (data) => {\\n  const msg = JSON.parse(data.toString());\\n  \\n  if (msg.id === 1 && msg.result) {\\n    // Authed — call tools/listMcp with confluence\\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({\\n      method: 'mcp.listTools',\\n      params: { server: 'confluence' },\\n      id: id++\\n    }));\\n  }\\n  \\n  if (msg.id >= 2 && msg.result !== undefined) {\\n    console.log(JSON.stringify(msg.result, null, 2));\\n    ws.close();\\n    process.exit(0);\\n  }\\n  \\n  if (msg.error) {\\n    console.log('ERROR:', JSON.stringify(msg.error));\\n    ws.close();\\n    process.exit(1);\\n  }\\n});\\n\\nws.on('error', (e) => {\\n  console.error('WS error:', e.message);\\n  process.exit(1);\\n});\\n\\nsetTimeout(() => {\\n  console.log('TIMEOUT - no response from gateway');\\n  ws.close();\\n  process.exit(1);\\n}, 20000);\\nEOF\",\n            \"workdir\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 18000,\n            \"timeout\": 25000\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979385292,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a7e7acd6beb270f7ba63cbe5025ee\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"54efbb14\",\n        \"seq\": 990\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The WebSocket API doesn't seem to support `mcp.listTools`. Let me try a different approach - check if the confluence MCP server is running by looking at the gateway logs.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_rgqun0wg2swd_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"# Check if confluence MCP started\\nps aux | grep confluence | grep -v grep\\necho \\\"---\\\"\\n# Check recent logs for confluence/startup\\ntail -100 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-12.log 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, json\\nfor line in sys.stdin:\\n    line = line.strip()\\n    try:\\n        d = json.loads(line)\\n        ts = d.get('time','')[:19]\\n        lvl = d.get('_meta',{}).get('logLevelName','')\\n        msg = ' '.join(str(d.get(str(i),'')) for i in range(5))\\n        if any(x in msg.lower() for x in ['confluence','conf','mcp','error','start','spawn','fork']):\\n            print(f'[{ts}][{lvl}] {msg[:200]}')\\n    except: pass\\n\\\" 2>/dev/null | tail -20\",\n            \"workdir\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 3000,\n            \"timeout\": 5000\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979428973,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a7eaa867121129e58d1006072ed14\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"ccf28612\",\n        \"seq\": 992\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The gateway keeps saying \\\"gateway already running under systemd; waiting 5000ms before retrying startup\\\". This means the `openclaw-gateway` service keeps trying to restart but something is preventing it. The new config is loaded but it says \\\"gateway already running\\\".\\n\\nBut the actual gateway process (358706) is running and it successfully reloaded the config with confluence at 07:36:02-07:36:03.\\n\\nThe issue is that there are two processes: `openclaw` (358696) and `openclaw-gateway` (358706). The `openclaw` process at 358696 is the one that keeps trying to start and failing with \\\"gateway already running\\\".\\n \\nSo the two processes are actually separate: `openclaw` at PID 358696 is the old gateway process from before 07:35, and `openclaw-gateway` at PID 358706 is the new one that restarted. The confusion is that `systemctl restart` spawned both, but only the new gateway process is active. My WebSocket test timed out because the auth method might be wrong, not because the gateway itself failed.\\n\\nLooking at the actual connection logs, there's a warning about an invalid handshake on the auth.anonymous frame, which suggests the authentication mechanism has changed. Rather than debugging the WebSocket connection further, I should test the confluence MCP directly by making a real API call to Confluence using the available tools.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"\\nGateway đang chạy ổn định. Test Confluence API trực tiếp:\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_90jqxql5uigu_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"curl -s -u \\\"ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com:ATATT3xFfGF0Xl6QZ-9lDBTiDym6FNGm1r6FJMt3u4ffIR8MjNDzl2oiKrRic_bdgOiIMWetDPY9FYMC_NPZ6O5uQVhiPip7oy2FlVGFqz5e214BGkaRoKmHz2XauaQG0A7rRq-7Lp8jp79Rdct2H61IouXCLFY4vQyXP9T9BPJT7ysxfnzJv7g=F3088272\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content?spaceKey=AW&limit=5&expand=body.storage,version\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Accept: application/json\\\" | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json, sys\\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\\nfor p in d.get('results', []):\\n    print(f\\\\\\\"  [{p['id']}] v{p['version']['number']}: {p['title']}\\\\\\\")\\n    body = p['body']['storage']['value'][:100]\\n    print(f\\\\\\\"    {body}...\\\\\\\")\\n\\\"\",\n            \"workdir\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 8000,\n            \"timeout\": 12000\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979439983,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a7eb1f0a5840b4a833c0070bbef09\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"1d4afe1e\",\n        \"seq\": 994\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The Confluence API is working correctly. Pages from the AW space are being retrieved.\\n\\nNow the question is: is the `confluence-mcp-server` npm package installed? Let me check if npx can find it. But first, let me understand the current status better.\\n\\nThe `confluence-mcp-server` npm package needs to be installed. It's installed via `npx -y confluence-mcp-server`. When the gateway tries to start it, it will download/install it. But the gateway is running and needs a restart to pick up the new `mcp.servers.confluence` config.\\n\\nBut wait - the gateway DID reload at 07:36:02. The INFO log says \\\"loading configuration\\\" and then \\\"starting\\\". Did it actually start the confluence MCP server?\\n\\n\\nLooking at the logs, the gateway tried to restart but hit the \\\"already running\\\" warning, which suggests the confluence MCP server might not have been initialized. Let me verify if it's actually running as a subprocess.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_6kivh2vq7beb_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"ps aux | grep -E \\\"mcp|confluence|node\\\" | grep -v grep | grep -v \\\"systemd\\\\|PID\\\"\",\n            \"workdir\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 3000,\n            \"timeout\": 5000\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979453281,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a7ebeae1d449b828b7f3bb4613505\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"87d7f41f\",\n        \"seq\": 996\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"I can see multiple `mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs` processes (one per cron run or agent session). But no `confluence-mcp-server` process. The confluence MCP server hasn't been started yet because the gateway needs to be restarted to pick up the new config.\\n\\nThe gateway is currently running with the old config (without confluence), and it's showing \\\"gateway already running under systemd\\\" because the new process can't take over the port. The gateway needs a proper restart.\\n\\nLet me force kill the old processes and restart properly. Actually, looking at this more carefully:\\n\\n- PIDs from 356908 to 358200 are old stitch MCP processes from 06:39 to 07:32\\n\\n\\n- PID 358833 is a new stitch MCP process from 07:37\\n- There's NO confluence MCP process at all\\n\\nThe gateway at PID 358706 doesn't have confluence spawned yet. I need to do a proper restart. Let me check the current gateway PID and restart it cleanly.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Confluence MCP chưa start. Cần restart sạch:\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_qxkh1m2xeibg_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"# Find the actual gateway PID\\nps aux | grep \\\"openclaw-gateway\\\" | grep -v grep\\necho \\\"---\\\"\\n# Kill all old stitch MCP processes (they're from cron runs, not the gateway)\\nkill $(ps aux | grep \\\"mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs\\\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}') 2>/dev/null\\necho \\\"Killed old stitch processes\\\"\\nsleep 2\\n# Now restart gateway cleanly\\nsystemctl stop openclaw-gateway\\nsleep 2\\nps aux | grep \\\"openclaw\\\" | grep -v grep | head -5\",\n            \"workdir\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 8000,\n            \"timeout\": 12000\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979460536,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a7ec55b3b27eeea7006e66b4c15ad\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"56be731e\",\n        \"seq\": 998\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Wait, there are TWO `openclaw-gateway` processes: PID 356713 and PID 358706. PID 356713 is from 06:36 and PID 358706 is from 07:35. When I ran `systemctl stop`, the old one (356713) is still running. This is the issue - there are TWO gateway instances!\\n\\nLet me stop and start properly.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_nbpw4l2chhqe_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"# Two gateways running! Kill both and restart cleanly\\nkill -9 356713 358706 2>/dev/null\\nsleep 3\\nsystemctl start openclaw-gateway\\nsleep 8\\nps aux | grep \\\"openclaw\\\" | grep -v grep\\necho \\\"---\\\"\\ntail -30 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-12.log 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys, json\\nfor line in sys.stdin:\\n    line = line.strip()\\n    try:\\n        d = json.loads(line)\\n        ts = d.get('time','')[:19]\\n        lvl = d.get('_meta',{}).get('logLevelName','')\\n        msg = ' '.join(str(d.get(str(i),'')) for i in range(5))\\n        print(f'[{ts}][{lvl}] {msg[:200]}')\\n    except: pass\\n\\\" 2>/dev/null | tail -15\",\n            \"workdir\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator\",\n            \"yieldMs\": 15000,\n            \"timeout\": 20000\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979475125,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a7ed4bd551868ee9c1ecb196d460b\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"53361567\",\n        \"seq\": 1000\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"gitlab có mcp không\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979676369,\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"b9e27ed1\",\n        \"seq\": 1001\n      },\n      \"senderLabel\": \"Khương Nịnh (6053576134)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The user is asking if GitLab has an MCP server. Let me give a quick answer.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Có. GitLab có MCP server chính thức:\\n\\n```\\nnpx -y @gitlab-org/mcp-gitlab\\n```\\n\\n**Các tools:**\\n- `gitlab_list_projects` — danh sách projects\\n- `gitlab_search` — tìm kiếm (code, issues, MRs)\\n- `gitlab_create_issue` — tạo issue\\n- `gitlab_create_mr` — tạo merge request\\n- `gitlab_list_mrs` — danh sách MRs\\n- `gitlab_view_diffs` — xem diff\\n\\n**Setup:**\\n```jsonc\\n{\\n  \\\"mcp\\\": {\\n    \\\"servers\\\": {\\n      \\\"gitlab\\\": {\\n        \\\"command\\\": \\\"npx\\\",\\n        \\\"args\\\": [\\\"-y\\\", \\\"@gitlab-org/mcp-gitlab\\\"],\\n        \\\"env\\\": {\\n          \\\"GITLAB_TOKEN\\\": \\\"your-gitlab-personal-access-token\\\",\\n          \\\"GITLAB_URL\\\": \\\"https://gitlab.com\\\"  // hoặc self-hosted URL\\n        }\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Lấy token:*** GitLab → Settings → Access Tokens → tạo token với scopes: `read_api`, `read_repository`, `write_repository`\\n\\nBạn muốn kết nối GitLab self-hosted hay gitlab.com? Nếu là instance riêng (như GitLab của công ty bạn), cho tôi URL và tôi viết config chính xác.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979676460,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a7f9eab7149d431704852e58fffc0\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"25e60760\",\n        \"seq\": 1002\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"🌅 Morning Pipeline Report — 12/04\\n\\nActive sessions: 4/34\\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\\n\\nSessions:\\n• master-orchestrator  → running (heartbeat)\\n• 5p Status Report     → running (subagent, spawned by cron)\\n• cron: 5p Progress    → done (last run 07:35 UTC)\\n• telegram:group       → done (last run 07:31 UTC)\\n• telegram:direct      → done (last run 07:28 UTC)\\n\\nAll agents: no failures, no blockers ✅\\nReady for new tasks.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979931455,\n      \"provenance\": {\n        \"kind\": \"inter_session\",\n        \"sourceSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:main\",\n        \"sourceTool\": \"sessions_send\"\n      },\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"370d9cfa\",\n        \"seq\": 1003\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"This is a cron report arriving from the group chat. The pipeline is healthy. No action needed - this is just an automated report. I should stay silent unless something needs attention.\\n\\nActually, looking at the HEARTBEAT.md instructions: \\\"If pipeline healthy: Stay silent (no noise to Khuowgn).\\\" But this is a cron report, not a heartbeat. The user is receiving this in the group. I should acknowledge it briefly.\\n\\nActually, this message is being delivered to me as a message. The user might be waiting for a response. But this is a scheduled report - I should reply briefly acknowledging it.\\n\\nWait - looking at the conversation flow, this is coming through as a message from the group chat. The user (Khuowgn) sent this as part of the conversation. \\n\\nThe report shows 4 active sessions with everything running smoothly, so I'll keep my response minimal and just confirm the status.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Pipeline healthy ✅ Báo cáo nhận được.\\n\\n**Tình trạng hiện tại:**\\n- Confluence MCP: đã add vào config, đang restart gateway để kích hoạt\\n- GitLab MCP: đang chờ bạn cung cấp URL + token nếu cần\\n\\nCần làm gì tiếp theo?\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775979931639,\n      \"responseId\": \"062a809db601b33376a4cef146a54e4e\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"fecbebba\",\n        \"seq\": 1004\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": true,\n  \"bytes\": 15243\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly. The process with PID 358696 is `openclaw` (not `openclaw-gateway`) and PID 358706 is `openclaw-gateway`. There are two processes:\n\n1. `openclaw` (PID 358696) - started at 07:35\n2. `openclaw-gateway` (PID 358706) - started at 07:35\n\nBoth started at 07:35 when I ran `systemctl restart`. The ERROR messages at 07:35:25 are from the new `openclaw` process trying to start with the old config (which still had `mcpServers`).\n \nThe reload at 07:35:28 picked up my config changes and detected the new confluence server, but the gateway couldn't fully restart because there were active operations running at the time. Then at 07:36:02, the gateway successfully reloaded the updated configuration.\n\nSo the gateway is actually running fine now with my new config that includes confluence. The ERROR logs I was seeing earlier were from before I removed `mcpServers` from the config. I should test whether the confluence MCP tools are actually working by making a direct MCP call through the gateway's WebSocket API."},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway đã reload thành công với `mcp.servers.confluence`. Test trực tiếp:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tvbx6yfm0m32_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"NODE_PATH=/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/node_modules node << 'EOF'\nconst WebSocket = require('ws');\n\nconst ws = new WebSocket('ws://127.0.0.1:18789');\nlet id = 1;\n\nws.on('open', () => {\n  ws.send(JSON.stringify({ method: 'auth.anonymous', params: {}, id: id++ }));\n});\n\nws.on('message', (data) => {\n  const msg = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n  \n  if (msg.id === 1 && msg.result) {\n    // Authed — call tools/listMcp with confluence\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n      method: 'mcp.listTools',\n      params: { server: 'confluence' },\n      id: id++\n    }));\n  }\n  \n  if (msg.id >= 2 && msg.result !== undefined) {\n    console.log(JSON.stringify(msg.result, null, 2));\n    ws.close();\n    process.exit(0);\n  }\n  \n  if (msg.error) {\n    console.log('ERROR:', JSON.stringify(msg.error));\n    ws.close();\n    process.exit(1);\n  }\n});\n\nws.on('error', (e) => {\n  console.error('WS error:', e.message);\n  process.exit(1);\n});\n\nsetTimeout(() => {\n  console.log('TIMEOUT - no response from gateway');\n  ws.close();\n  process.exit(1);\n}, 20000);\nEOF","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator","yieldMs":18000,"timeout":25000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979385292,"responseId":"062a7e7acd6beb270f7ba63cbe5025ee","__openclaw":{"id":"54efbb14","seq":990}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The WebSocket API doesn't seem to support `mcp.listTools`. Let me try a different approach - check if the confluence MCP server is running by looking at the gateway logs."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rgqun0wg2swd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if confluence MCP started\nps aux | grep confluence | grep -v grep\necho \"---\"\n# Check recent logs for confluence/startup\ntail -100 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-12.log 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.strip()\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        ts = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        lvl = d.get('_meta',{}).get('logLevelName','')\n        msg = ' '.join(str(d.get(str(i),'')) for i in range(5))\n        if any(x in msg.lower() for x in ['confluence','conf','mcp','error','start','spawn','fork']):\n            print(f'[{ts}][{lvl}] {msg[:200]}')\n    except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null | tail -20","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator","yieldMs":3000,"timeout":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979428973,"responseId":"062a7eaa867121129e58d1006072ed14","__openclaw":{"id":"ccf28612","seq":992}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway keeps saying \"gateway already running under systemd; waiting 5000ms before retrying startup\". This means the `openclaw-gateway` service keeps trying to restart but something is preventing it. The new config is loaded but it says \"gateway already running\".\n\nBut the actual gateway process (358706) is running and it successfully reloaded the config with confluence at 07:36:02-07:36:03.\n\nThe issue is that there are two processes: `openclaw` (358696) and `openclaw-gateway` (358706). The `openclaw` process at 358696 is the one that keeps trying to start and failing with \"gateway already running\".\n \nSo the two processes are actually separate: `openclaw` at PID 358696 is the old gateway process from before 07:35, and `openclaw-gateway` at PID 358706 is the new one that restarted. The confusion is that `systemctl restart` spawned both, but only the new gateway process is active. My WebSocket test timed out because the auth method might be wrong, not because the gateway itself failed.\n\nLooking at the actual connection logs, there's a warning about an invalid handshake on the auth.anonymous frame, which suggests the authentication mechanism has changed. Rather than debugging the WebSocket connection further, I should test the confluence MCP directly by making a real API call to Confluence using the available tools."},{"type":"text","text":"\nGateway đang chạy ổn định. Test Confluence API trực tiếp:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_90jqxql5uigu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -u \"ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com:ATATT3xFfGF0Xl6QZ-9lDBTiDym6FNGm1r6FJMt3u4ffIR8MjNDzl2oiKrRic_bdgOiIMWetDPY9FYMC_NPZ6O5uQVhiPip7oy2FlVGFqz5e214BGkaRoKmHz2XauaQG0A7rRq-7Lp8jp79Rdct2H61IouXCLFY4vQyXP9T9BPJT7ysxfnzJv7g=F3088272\" \\\n  \"https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content?spaceKey=AW&limit=5&expand=body.storage,version\" \\\n  -H \"Accept: application/json\" | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor p in d.get('results', []):\n    print(f\\\"  [{p['id']}] v{p['version']['number']}: {p['title']}\\\")\n    body = p['body']['storage']['value'][:100]\n    print(f\\\"    {body}...\\\")\n\"","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator","yieldMs":8000,"timeout":12000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979439983,"responseId":"062a7eb1f0a5840b4a833c0070bbef09","__openclaw":{"id":"1d4afe1e","seq":994}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Confluence API is working correctly. Pages from the AW space are being retrieved.\n\nNow the question is: is the `confluence-mcp-server` npm package installed? Let me check if npx can find it. But first, let me understand the current status better.\n\nThe `confluence-mcp-server` npm package needs to be installed. It's installed via `npx -y confluence-mcp-server`. When the gateway tries to start it, it will download/install it. But the gateway is running and needs a restart to pick up the new `mcp.servers.confluence` config.\n\nBut wait - the gateway DID reload at 07:36:02. The INFO log says \"loading configuration\" and then \"starting\". Did it actually start the confluence MCP server?\n\n\nLooking at the logs, the gateway tried to restart but hit the \"already running\" warning, which suggests the confluence MCP server might not have been initialized. Let me verify if it's actually running as a subprocess."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6kivh2vq7beb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep -E \"mcp|confluence|node\" | grep -v grep | grep -v \"systemd\\|PID\"","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator","yieldMs":3000,"timeout":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979453281,"responseId":"062a7ebeae1d449b828b7f3bb4613505","__openclaw":{"id":"87d7f41f","seq":996}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see multiple `mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs` processes (one per cron run or agent session). But no `confluence-mcp-server` process. The confluence MCP server hasn't been started yet because the gateway needs to be restarted to pick up the new config.\n\nThe gateway is currently running with the old config (without confluence), and it's showing \"gateway already running under systemd\" because the new process can't take over the port. The gateway needs a proper restart.\n\nLet me force kill the old processes and restart properly. Actually, looking at this more carefully:\n\n- PIDs from 356908 to 358200 are old stitch MCP processes from 06:39 to 07:32\n\n\n- PID 358833 is a new stitch MCP process from 07:37\n- There's NO confluence MCP process at all\n\nThe gateway at PID 358706 doesn't have confluence spawned yet. I need to do a proper restart. Let me check the current gateway PID and restart it cleanly."},{"type":"text","text":"Confluence MCP chưa start. Cần restart sạch:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qxkh1m2xeibg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Find the actual gateway PID\nps aux | grep \"openclaw-gateway\" | grep -v grep\necho \"---\"\n# Kill all old stitch MCP processes (they're from cron runs, not the gateway)\nkill $(ps aux | grep \"mcp-stitch-key/server.mjs\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}') 2>/dev/null\necho \"Killed old stitch processes\"\nsleep 2\n# Now restart gateway cleanly\nsystemctl stop openclaw-gateway\nsleep 2\nps aux | grep \"openclaw\" | grep -v grep | head -5","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator","yieldMs":8000,"timeout":12000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979460536,"responseId":"062a7ec55b3b27eeea7006e66b4c15ad","__openclaw":{"id":"56be731e","seq":998}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, there are TWO `openclaw-gateway` processes: PID 356713 and PID 358706. PID 356713 is from 06:36 and PID 358706 is from 07:35. When I ran `systemctl stop`, the old one (356713) is still running. This is the issue - there are TWO gateway instances!\n\nLet me stop and start properly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nbpw4l2chhqe_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Two gateways running! Kill both and restart cleanly\nkill -9 356713 358706 2>/dev/null\nsleep 3\nsystemctl start openclaw-gateway\nsleep 8\nps aux | grep \"openclaw\" | grep -v grep\necho \"---\"\ntail -30 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-12.log 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.strip()\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        ts = d.get('time','')[:19]\n        lvl = d.get('_meta',{}).get('logLevelName','')\n        msg = ' '.join(str(d.get(str(i),'')) for i in range(5))\n        print(f'[{ts}][{lvl}] {msg[:200]}')\n    except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null | tail -15","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979475125,"responseId":"062a7ed4bd551868ee9c1ecb196d460b","__openclaw":{"id":"53361567","seq":1000}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"gitlab có mcp không"}],"timestamp":1775979676369,"__openclaw":{"id":"b9e27ed1","seq":1001},"senderLabel":"Khương Nịnh (6053576134)"},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if GitLab has an MCP server. Let me give a quick answer."},{"type":"text","text":"Có. GitLab có MCP server chính thức:\n\n```\nnpx -y @gitlab-org/mcp-gitlab\n```\n\n**Các tools:**\n- `gitlab_list_projects` — danh sách projects\n- `gitlab_search` — tìm kiếm (code, issues, MRs)\n- `gitlab_create_issue` — tạo issue\n- `gitlab_create_mr` — tạo merge request\n- `gitlab_list_mrs` — danh sách MRs\n- `gitlab_view_diffs` — xem diff\n\n**Setup:**\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"mcp\": {\n    \"servers\": {\n      \"gitlab\": {\n        \"command\": \"npx\",\n        \"args\": [\"-y\", \"@gitlab-org/mcp-gitlab\"],\n        \"env\": {\n          \"GITLAB_TOKEN\": \"your-gitlab-personal-access-token\",\n          \"GITLAB_URL\": \"https://gitlab.com\"  // hoặc self-hosted URL\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Lấy token:*** GitLab → Settings → Access Tokens → tạo token với scopes: `read_api`, `read_repository`, `write_repository`\n\nBạn muốn kết nối GitLab self-hosted hay gitlab.com? Nếu là instance riêng (như GitLab của công ty bạn), cho tôi URL và tôi viết config chính xác."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775979676460,"responseId":"062a7f9eab7149d431704852e58fffc0","__openclaw":{"id":"25e60760","seq":1002}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🌅 Morning Pipeline Report — 12/04\n\nActive sessions: 4/34\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n\nSessions:\n• master-orchestrator  → running (heartbeat)\n• 5p Status Report     → running (subagent, spawned by cron)\n• cron: 5p Progress    → done (last run 07:35 UTC)\n• telegram:group       → done (last run 07:31 UTC)\n• telegram:direct      → done (last run 07:28 UTC)\n\nAll agents: no failures, no blockers ✅\nReady for new tasks."}],"timestamp":1775979931455,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:main","sourceTool":"sessions_send"},"__openclaw":{"id":"370d9cfa","seq":1003}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a cron report arriving from the group chat. The pipeline is healthy. No action needed - this is just an automated report. I should stay silent unless something needs attention.\n\nActually, looking at the HEARTBEAT.md instructions: \"If pipeline healthy: Stay silent (no noise to Khuowgn).\" But this is a cron report, not a heartbeat. The user is receiving this in the group. I should acknowledge it briefly.\n\nActually, this message is being delivered to me as a message. The user might be waiting for a response. But this is a scheduled report - I should reply briefly acknowledging it.\n\nWait - looking at the conversation flow, this is coming through as a message from the group chat. The user (Khuowgn) sent this as part of the conversation. \n\nThe report shows 4 active sessions with everything running smoothly, so I'll keep my response minimal and just confirm the status."},{"type":"text","text":"Pipeline healthy ✅ Báo cáo nhận được.\n\n**Tình trạng hiện tại:**\n- Confluence MCP: đã add vào config, đang restart gateway để kích hoạt\n- GitLab MCP: đang chờ bạn cung cấp URL + token nếu cần\n\nCần làm gì tiếp theo?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775979931639,"responseId":"062a809db601b33376a4cef146a54e4e","__openclaw":{"id":"fecbebba","seq":1004}}],"truncated":true,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":true,"contentRedacted":true,"bytes":15243},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775979986865}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0bc5242","parentId":"926e427e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:46:36.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full context. Lead has:\n1. Confluence MCP: added to config, gateway restart in progress\n2. GitLab MCP: needs URL + token from Lead\n\nMy pending tasks from MEMORY.md:\n- Stitch MCP async polling\n- Stitch stitch-connect skill update\n\nBut Lead's priority right now seems to be the MCP setup (Confluence + GitLab). Let me check the current status of the gateway and confluence MCP.\n\nActually, looking at the history, the last activity was about restarting the gateway to activate Confluence MCP. Let me check current status and provide options.\n\nThe key question: What does Lead want to do next? They asked \"Cần làm gì tiếp theo?\"\n\n\nLead is waiting on me to finish activating the Confluence MCP, so I should check the gateway status and let them know the next steps for GitLab configuration.","thinkingSignature":"cfa7395c72f646de29ef70b4beb38f0977a93126b2cf4b61e2f61a9d8a487e04"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8cnnl30wcyfj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep \"openclaw\" | grep -v grep\necho \"---\"\nps aux | grep \"confluence\" | grep -v grep\necho \"---\"\ncat /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('MCP servers:', list(d.get('mcp',{}).get('servers',{}).keys()))\"","timeout":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":5296,"output":305,"cacheRead":15148,"cacheWrite":618,"totalTokens":21367,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775979987127,"responseId":"062a80d38bfcfcad16a6d208371fcbc2"}}
