{"type":"message","id":"ecd11a9b","parentId":"839bed5a","timestamp":"2026-04-12T09:14:47.714Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-12 08:46:48 UTC] Pipeline is healthy. Staying silent per protocol — no message sent to group.\nSystem: [2026-04-12 08:49:41 UTC] **HEARTBEAT_CHECK: PASSED — but 1 blocker detected.**\nSystem: \nSystem: 🟡 Orbis — 5p Status | 08:49 UTC 12 Apr\nSystem: \nSystem: ✅ Pipeline: MOSTLY HEALTHY (1 blocker)\nSystem: • Active sessions: **3** | master-orchestrator × 2, cron-session × 1\nSystem: • Review pipeline: **COMPLETE** (6/6 agents finished)\nSystem: • `code-reviewer` subagent: **FAILED** ❌ — stopped at 08:24 UTC\nSystem:   → Reason: `500 Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')`\nSystem:   → MCP server error (not code-reviewer logic)\nSystem:   → Reports likely already written by sibling agents\nSystem: • `database-reviewer`, `performance-optimizer`: errors in messages but status=done\nSystem: • MCP servers: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\nSystem: • Cron jobs: 2 active (5p every 5m | Daily @ 5AM+7)\nSystem: • Blockers: **1** (`code-reviewer` failed — non-critical, pipeline done)\nSystem: \nSystem: ---\nSystem: \nSystem: **Recommendation**: `code-reviewer` failure is a **known MCP error**, not a code logic failure. The sibling agents (`senior-backend`, `security-reviewer`, `senior-frontend`) completed their reviews. Consider restarting `code-reviewer` separately if its report is needed.\nSystem: [2026-04-12 08:55:53 UTC] The report was delivered via cron job announcement mechanism. Here's the summary:\nSystem: \nSystem: ---\nSystem: \nSystem: 🟡 Orbis — 5p Status | 08:54 UTC 12 Apr\nSystem: \nSystem: 🔴 Pipeline: **DEGRADED**\nSystem: • Active sessions: 11 | Running agents: **0 active**\nSystem: • Subagents (this cycle):\nSystem:   - `code-reviewer` ❌ **FAILED**\nSystem:   - `performance-optimizer` ❌ **FAILED** (500: providerSpecificData)\nSystem:   - `database-reviewer` ❌ **FAI